@da-woods I guess it depends on what the general strategy is for handling backwards compatibility. If I ran

```
class A:
  def __class_getitem__(cls, item):
    return item

print(A[2])
```

on Python 3.6 I should get a TypeError which I would no longer get without the python3.7 guard.

@scoder will update to use `__Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr` as suggested.

